------------------------------------------------------------
DOCUMENT OBJECTIVE
------------------------------------------------------------

Produce a comprehensive engineering specification that explains the framework, not merely the code.

The document should allow an experienced developer to understand:

• what the framework does

• how it is organized

• why it is organized that way

• how every major subsystem interacts

• how data flows

• how processing flows

• how configuration controls behavior

• how templates control formatting

• how synchronization occurs

• how reports are produced

• how validation operates

• how governance is enforced

------------------------------------------------------------
DOCUMENT STYLE
------------------------------------------------------------

Write as an engineering specification.

Do not write a user manual.

Do not explain JavaScript syntax.

Do not document every line of code.

Document architecture, framework behavior, engineering decisions, and implementation standards.

Use formal technical language.

Avoid historical references unless documenting an approved governance decision.

Document only the current framework.

